name: phosphoenolpyruvate carboxylase
comment: This enzyme replenishes oxaloacetate in the tricarboxylic acid cycle when operating in the reverse direction. The reaction proceeds in two steps: formation of carboxyphosphate and the enolate form of pyruvate, followed by carboxylation of the enolate and release of phosphate.

references.title: Multiple forms of phosphoenolpyruvate carboxylase from Chlamydomonas reeinhardtii.
Carbon Dioxide Fixation into Oxalacetate in Higher Plants.
